<section id="fs-id742248" class="conceptual-questions" type="conceptual-questions">
<title>Conceptual Questions</title>
    <exercise id="fs-id3028270" type="conceptual-questions"><problem id="fs-id2653181">
    <para id="import-auto-id2671466">What two pieces of evidence allowed the first calculation of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>e</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{m"" lSub { size 8{e} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>, the mass of the electron? </para><para id="import-auto-id1579291">(a) The ratios <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>q</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>e</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">/</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>e</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{q rSub { size 8{e} } /m rSub { size 8{e} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> and <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>q</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>p</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">/</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>p</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{q rSub { size 8{p} } /m rSub { size 8{p} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>.</para>
    <para id="import-auto-id1561600">(b) The values of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>q</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>e</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{q rSub { size 8{e} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> and <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>E</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>B</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{E rSub { size 8{B} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>. </para>
    <para id="import-auto-id2456089">(c) The ratio <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>q</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>e</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">/</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>e</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{q rSub { size 8{e} } /m rSub { size 8{e} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> and <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>q</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>e</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{q rSub { size 8{e} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>.</para>
    <para id="import-auto-id3233376">Justify your response.</para>
    </problem></exercise>
      
