    <exercise id="fs-id3119625" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id2403605">
      <para id="import-auto-id1945478">Rutherford found the size of the nucleus to be about <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mtext>15</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext> m</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"10" rSup { size 8{ - "15"} } " m"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>. This implied a huge density. What would this density be for gold?</para></problem>

